Sub-Sahara Africa Stocks: Custodian & Allied, Dangote Sugar Refinery Move

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-03-01T15:28:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/sub-sahara-africa-stocks-custodian-allied-dangote-sugar-refinery-move.html
Mauritius’s SEMDEX Index declined
for a second day, losing 0.1 percent to 2,024.74 by the 1:30
p.m. close in  Port Louis .  Kenya’s All-Share Index retreated 0.3 percent to 77.25 by
the 3 p.m. close in Nairobi, a second day of decreases. The
Nigerian Stock Exchange All-Share Index retreated for a fifth
day, dropping 0.6 percent to 25,869.32 by 2:32 p.m. in Lagos,
while the Ghana Stock Exchange Composite Index lost less than
0.1 percent to 1,051.36 by 2:22 p.m. in Accra. Namibia’s
FTSE  Namibia Overall Index  gained for a third day, adding 0.3
percent to 898.64 by 4:22 p.m. in Windhoek.  The following shares rose or fell in sub-Saharan Africa,
excluding  South Africa . Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Custodian & Allied Insurance Plc (CUSTODYI NL), a Nigerian
insurer, dropped 17 kobo, or 4.8 percent, to 3.34 naira. The
company’s recommendation was cut to “accumulate” from “buy”
at Vetiva Capital Management Ltd.    Dangote Sugar Refinery Plc  (DANGSUGA NL), a Nigerian maker
of the sweetener, dropped to the lowest since March 2009, losing
67 kobo, or 4.6 percent, to 13.87 naira. Sugar for May delivery
snapped three days of gains, losing as much as 3 percent to
28.58 cents a pound on ICE Futures U.S. in New York.  To contact the reporters on this story:
